{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\n\nThe default test suite runs serially with branch coverage — the dominant cost of the\n`build-and-test` job (~22 min pytest). Measured `pytest -n4 --dist worksteal` on the same\nselection is ~5× faster (1700s→~350s) with byte-identical outcomes (5877P/14S/same 1\nknown-Py3.14 fail), proving the suite's per-test isolation holds under parallel workers.\n\n## What\n\nIntroduce pytest-xdist to the gating test runs, pinned to the runner's real core count.\n\n- Add `pytest-xdist` and `pytest-split` to the `[dev]` extra in `pyproject.toml`, pinned\n  exactly (both are ABSENT today; used ad hoc in experiments only).\n- `gerrit-verify.yaml` + `test.yml`: change the default-suite command to\n  `pytest -m \"not integration and not external\" -n <N> --dist worksteal …` where N is the\n  runner's real vCPU count — pin `-n4` (ubuntu-latest, 4 vCPU) / `-n3` (macos arm, 3 vCPU),\n  NOT `-n auto` (18-worker local runs over-subscribe and hit a coverage SQLite combine race).\n- FIX COVERAGE UNDER XDIST (prereq — proven): add `parallel = true` to\n  `[tool.coverage.run]` in `pyproject.toml`. Without it, `-n4 --cov` fails to combine\n  worker data (reports ~37% vs the true 80%, below `fail_under=70` → red build, and leaks\n  `.coverage.*` files). With `parallel = true` the combined TOTAL matches serial exactly.\n- Integration tier: parallelize only NON-live tests. `pytest -m \"integration and not live\n  and not jira_live\" -n4` is xdist-safe (64P/1S identical serial vs -n4, 1.6× faster).\n  Live tests (`[integration, live]`, e.g. `test_reconcile_live_e2e.py`) share one live Jira\n  project and flake under parallel load (eventual-consistency); keep them serial or confine\n  to one worker via `@pytest.mark.xdist_group` + `--dist loadgroup`. In CI's integration job\n  they self-skip without Jira creds, but the command must not assume that.\n- Update `docs/coverage.md` to document that coverage collection under pytest-xdist REQUIRES\n  `parallel = true` in `[tool.coverage.run]` (else the combined TOTAL is silently deflated,\n  e.g. ~37% vs the true 80%, tripping `fail_under`), so anyone adding a new coverage-bearing\n  workflow keeps the combine correct. This satisfies the parent epic's AC-3.\n\n## Scope\n\n- Files: `pyproject.toml` (`[dev]` deps, `[tool.coverage.run] parallel`),\n  `.github/workflows/gerrit-verify.yaml`, `.github/workflows/test.yml`, `docs/coverage.md`.\n- Verify runner vCPU with an in-workflow `nproc` echo (belt-and-suspenders) before pinning N.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `pytest-xdist` + `pytest-split` added to `[dev]`, pinned exactly.\n- [ ] `parallel = true` added to `[tool.coverage.run]`; a `-n4 --cov` run reports a combined\n      TOTAL equal to the serial value and ≥ `fail_under=70`, with no `.coverage.*` files left\n      in the checkout.\n- [ ] gerrit-verify + test.yml default-suite step runs with `-n <real-cores> --dist worksteal`;\n      test outcomes are identical to the pre-change serial run (same pass/skip counts, no new\n      isolation/leak-guard failures).\n- [ ] Non-live integration tier runs under `-n4`; live tests are kept serial or xdist_group-confined.\n- [ ] `docs/coverage.md` updated to document the xdist + `parallel=true` coverage-combine\n      requirement (satisfies parent AC-3).\n- [ ] Change passes CI (`Verified +1`) and lands via Gerrit."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783966982075974001,"uuid":"ce2abe06-475f-4517-b35e-9909662d276e"}